ner","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":20.1,"toNextMi":11,"note":"Junction toward Brunswick & Portland","control":["Brunswick","Portland","Augusta","Lewiston","USVA Togus","Randolph SR 24 Richmond"],"lat":44.95036,"lng":-69.86077,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":6,"place":"Augusta","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":31.1,"toNextMi":17.2,"note":"Junction toward Winthrop SR 8 north","control":["Winthrop SR 8 north","Randolph","Rockland SR 105 east (Cony Street East) Windsor","China","Augusta Civic Center Drive","Portland","Belfast"],"lat":44.95036,"lng":-69.86077,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":7,"place":"Winslow","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":48.3,"toNextMi":1.7,"note":"Junction toward Kennedy Memorial Drive & Oakland","control":["Kennedy Memorial Drive","Oakland","China","Clinton","Burnham"],"lat":44.95036,"lng":-69.86077,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":8,"place":"Waterville","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":50,"toNextMi":3.6,"note":"Junction toward Oakland","control":["Oakland","Sidney"],"lat":44.95036,"lng":-69.86077,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":9,"place":"Fairfield","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":53.6,"toNextMi":15.3,"note":"","control":["Norridgewock","Bangor","Augusta","Oakland","Canaan"],"lat":44.95036,"lng":-69.86077,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":10,"place":"Skowhegan","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":68.9,"toNextMi":4.7,"note":"Junction toward Norridgewock SR 104 Fairfield Center","control":["Norridgewock SR 104 Fairfield Center"],"lat":44.95036,"lng":-69.86077,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":11,"place":"Madison","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":73.6,"toNextMi":10.7,"note":"Junction toward Madison","control":["Madison","Athens"],"lat":44.95036,"lng":-69.86077,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":12,"place":"Solon","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":84.3,"toNextMi":7.8,"note":"Junction toward North Anson & Madison","control":["North Anson","Madison"],"lat":44.95036,"lng":-69.86077,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":13,"place":"Bingham","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":92.1,"toNextMi":48.9,"note":"","control":["Abbot"],"lat":45.02961,"lng":-69.85784,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":14,"place":"Jackman","state":"ME","kind":"town","mileFromStart":141,"toNextMi":16.4,"note":"Junction toward Rockwood & Greenville","control":["Rockwood","Greenville"],"lat":45.60443,"lng":-70.19952,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":15,"place":"Sandy Bay","state":"ME","kind":"terminus","mileFromStart":157.4,"toNextMi":null,"note":"The drive ends here","control":["Saint-Georges","Québec"],"lat":45.76209,"lng":-70.31045,"src":"wikipedia"}],"history":{"paragraphs":["US 201 follows old river trading routes of the Abenaki people. Parts of Benedict Arnold's expedition to Quebec took place along the route that today make up US 201. On June 15, 2000, the route was designated a National Scenic Byway.","US 201 used to be New England Interstate Route 20 (NEI 20) in the 1920s. The original 1922 plan had NEI 20 starting in Portland. The southern half was later shifted east to start in Brunswick (the realignment may have been done prior to actual signing of the route.) The southern end of the original NEI 20 is now SR 100 from Portland to Augusta.[citation needed] The Brunswick end of the original NEI 20 intersected with NEI 1 (which is now US 1), which remained the southern terminus of US 201 until the construction of the US 1 freeway, at which point its terminus was moved to its current location on SR 24.","Since its designation in 1926, US 201 has only undergone one major realignment. The original highway used to run through Norridgewock, Anson, and Madison on its way to Solon. In 1954, US 201 was moved to a new eastern alignment which completely bypasses this area and the existing alignment was redesignated US 201A. US 201 has also undergone various other minor route adjustments, but largely maintains its original 1926 routing."],"sourceSection":"History","src":"wikipedia"},"highlights":[{"n":"Brunswick","d":"The drive begins here","q":"Brunswick","lat":43.89416667,"lng":-69.97777778,"src":"wikipedia"},{"n":"Sandy Bay","d":"The drive ends here","q":"Sandy Bay","lat":45.93333333,"lng":-69.86666667,"src":"wikipedia"}],"references":[{"n":1,"text":"U.S. Numbered Highways – 1989 Edition (current). AASHTO. Retrieved 13 July 2012.","url":"http://www.transportation.org/sites/route/docs/USRN-page101_186.pdf"},{"n":2,"text":"Scenic Byway Archived June 24, 2012, at the Wayback Machine. visitmaine.com. Retrieved 13 July 2012.","url":"http://www.visitmaine.com/attractions/sightseeing_tours/scenic_byway/"},{"n":3,"text":"Maine Scenic Drives: Old Canada Road Scenic Byway. HowStuffWorks. Retrieved 14 July 2012.","url":"http://tlc.howstuffworks.com/family/scenic-drive-in-maine-old-canada-road-scenic-byway-ga1.htm"},{"n":4,"text":"Gibson, John (1998). Maine's Most Scenic Roads: 25 Routes Off the Beaten Path. Camden, Maine: Down East Books. pp. 123–130.","url":""},{"n":5,"text":"Old Canada Road Scenic Byway (Route 201) Archived July 12, 2012, at the Wayback Machine. exploremaine.org. Retrieved 13 July 2012.","url":"http://www.exploremaine.org/byways/kennebec/old-canada-rd.shtml"},{"n":6,"text":"Old Canada Road Scenic Byway – Official Designations Archived March 10, 2007, at the Wayback Machine. byways.org. Retrieved 13 July 2012.","url":"http://byways.org/explore/byways/11510/designation.html"},{"n":7,"text":"\"MaineDOT Public Map Viewer\". Maine Department of Transportation. Retrieved April 10, 2017.","url":"http://www.maine.gov/mdot/mapviewer/"}],"routeLine":[[44.95036,-69.86077],[44.95093,-69.86106],[44.95169,-69.86113],[44.95355,-69.86122],[44.95527,-69.86135],[44.95697,-69.86149],[44.95758,-69.86154],[44.95859,-69.86162],[44.96003,-69.86182],[44.96125,-69.86198],[44.96342,-69.8623],[44.96486,-69.86257],[44.96555,-69.86273],[44.9666,-69.86302],[44.9673,-69.86325],[44.9685,-69.86361],[44.96921,-69.86383],[44.9701,-69.8641],[44.97099,-69.86437],[44.97246,-69.86483],[44.97348,-69.86513],[44.97472,-69.86551],[4